caption: D’Andrews is the perfect spot is you’re looking for a coffee, good breakfast, or something sweet! I’ve been many times and always have a wonderful experience. You can’t go wrong with anything on the menu!
They are good specialists in baking and their products are worthy of the competition !!
The cream filled doughnut might as well be from Paris. Out of this world.

I was in town for the weekend with my husband and went here because I was craving pastry. We got some cookies and other yummy looking pastries. Not sure what we got because they all looked delicious. I told my husband to buy what  looked …
Absolutely adorable cafe, wonderful staff, and the pastries are beautiful!! The strawberry croquette was light and delicious. We also loved the mocha torte and carrot cake. Go here!!

Wonderful, peaceful cafe. Gourmet pastries that are beautifully displayed - my personal favorite being the pistachio- cherry jam croissant. Best part of my experience was most definitely my refreshing cup of the most pure, shimmering cup of water I've ever had.  10/10

Impeccable quality, the freshest and most delicious breakfast sandwich I've ever had!! Pastries were AMAZING!! So glad we stopped by happy accident!! The pride of workmanship is very apparent!! Thank you!
Pastry was a little bland.

The best cafe/bakery downtown.  All the standards are great (love the flaky croissants), but I especially adore the falafel.  Its deliciousness is unexpected and unusual (pickled cauliflower, carrot humus!).  The falafel makes clear that in addition to pastry skills, the folks in the kitchen have some serious flavor chops.
Wonderful food!! Fresh and tasty!! A must do if in the area!!

I'm town for work and this has quickly become my mandatory morning routine. The coffee, soup, and sandwich are all fantastic and I'll definitely be back to try the pastries as they look incredible as well.
Quality Cakes Good prices They derived to Restaurant
Best croissant I've ever had. Holy moly.
Great baked goods and coffee. Bit pricey, but worth it!

The pastry/ bakery items here are ridiculously good, and can’t adequately be explained in a google review. But, with that being said, I keep going back for the coffee. I really appreciate some place that makes a good cup of black coffee. They don’t mask everything with syrups and sugars, great coffee!

I work in town and legitimately come here everyday , I’ve  had the different iced coffees and teas and other coffees  , everything’s awesome . Also best bathroom downtown , pants down . With the good tp. I appreciates that 💩🚽
Everything was very good and staff was very friendly!

This bakery is the go to location for me on Sundays - or any day that ends in Y. Elevated bakery items from the double baked croissant or the savory bread pudding with Tennessee prosciutto to the made to order breakfast sandwiches. Sit on …

My daughter had her eyes set on visiting this bakery after searching for bakeries in Nashville. Once we arrived we decided to try some of their sandwiches too. The sandwiches and cookies were amazing. We highly recommend a visit here if you are in the downtown Nashville area.
Best breakfast place in town!
Go here! Biscuits, pastries and sandwiches to die for. Highly recommended. Great service and fantastic staff.

Heard about their legendary croissants so I ordered some for pickup. Drove from Spring Hill to Nashville to pick up my order and they sold them out from under me.  Got a refund, but don’t order online.  They won’t fulfill it.
Amazing pastries and sandwiches. Definitely a foodie place in downtown Nashville!

Carbs yes!!!! If you think Publix bakery is good, prepare to ruin your taste buds. The baked goods are hands down the best ive ever had. They WILL ruin you for the grocery store. We weren't actually prepared for that. My wife and children are now spoiled and Publix is no longer an option.
Great food
OMG. Must stop here. This isn't a bakery its an Culinary Experience of a Lifetime. Best Bakery in the World!
Good food and service.
No decaf available, around $30 for 3 coffees and 3 pastries. Average experience

If you are looking for HIGH QUALITY tea in Nashville, this is the place to go. Haven’t found another place that matches the quality of the tea and the attention to detail with the tea is amazing with no bitterness at all. Very impressed!!
Great coffee and excellent food. Just crushed the chicken sausage sandwich and it was A+

First time there today—went to make a large order for my office. Didn’t really know the menu all that well and they were nothing but kind, no rushing in ordering. Sandwiches were made fresh and quickly. Now, I should take a point away cause …
Yummy!!!
Nice little bakery with some delicious treats!  The flies were annoying, it could be a little cleaner.

After a long trip to Nashville my family and I were in desperate need of coffee, we found this cute establishment and we decided to try it. Ingredients are wholesome and they use real dairy and great coffee which is very important to us. We …

Smoke and mirrors, man. Staff is friendly and Cafe is clean, but the cake is subpar. I bought a cake here for my fiance's birthday and it neither looked great nor tasted great. Maybe they have different flavors that are better but if you ask me, I say hard pass on this bakery.
Yummy food

My family and I love D'Andrews. Their made fresh every day bakery items are 2nd to none. They also have a terrific breakfast and lunch menu, and assorted coffees. David and his staff are all great people who work very hard to provide excellent service and freshly made food.
Insider tip. The 4th of July box with s’mores and pork belly sliders was amazing.
Amazing bakery. All the pastries we had were fantastic, as was the coffee.
Great fresh food, and the guy suggested their Nitro coffee, which was spot on perfect for a summer lunch!

I'm perhaps the biggest fan of D'Andrews there is. The food is always perfect and the staff has bent over backwards to help me in a pinch. They might have the best croissants in all of Nashville! Definitely try them out- you won't be disappointed.
Great coffee and pastries. The owner has all the heart to make this unforgettable

This is a cute little coffee spot for a visit with friends or just somewhere to pop in for a to-go drink. It’s a little pricey and there’s unfortunately no free parking. Otherwise, an enjoyable experience.
Fantastic coffee, pastries and just the nicest service....plus the ambiance has a great European Cafe vibe
Excellent breakfast sandwiches, great pastries, friendly ownership
Best cake! Ask them to make ANYTHING and they are also kind enough to deliver for you!

Delightful café and bakery nestled in the heart of Nashville. I walked there from the library for coffee and a treat, on one of my visits to Tennessee. I had the nitro cold brew and a donut, I would not hesitate to order both of those again. Five stars, well worth the visit!

This is a great location. Very creative with beautiful decorating skills. I called on monday night asking for a design for 36 cupcakes. D'andrew was very patient and kind. I have never eaten at this bakery but saw the great reviews. I …
People should go there immediately. The food was extraordinary.  Left there with several pastries for later.
da ansrew is veri nice. he sel me fod and now i not hangry!!!1
Super place for breakfast and nice staff

I had a wonderful experience ordering pastries for my son's birthday today.  He is a first year student at Vanderbilt.  I called yesterday and they customized an order for me, delivered the order this afternoon and helped me make his …
D'Andrews is fantastic.  Road tripping towards Atlanta and found this gem.  Highly recommended
My husband and I pop in when we visit Nashville. Always on point. Highly recommend having any sweet. You can taste the love!

I decided to come alone and it was very relaxed. It wasnt crowded but it was also on a Monday in January so... I do think I found my new lunch spot! There is parking right across the street and the owner's cute frenchie named Stacy is an amazing mascot.
Excellent pastries and friendly staff. Prices were fairly reasonable.
Delicious
Awkward humorless team serving overpriced coffee in a sanitary but bland atmosphere. Medium is their large and no refill price

Served old coffee and server picked out the blue berry corn meal muffin with one blueberry- i should have picked. And the smallest chocolate croissant- again i should have picked and not cheap. And the prosciutto riccota had no prosciutto …
OMG so yum!! Their signature donut w cream!! Holy cow!
A bit expensive but the amazing sandwiches are worth it. Love their BLT and Bacon Eggg and Cheese sandwiches.
Best veggie egg white breakfast sandwich and pecan cinnamon roll I’ve ever had.   This place is amazing!
Great bakery. Surpassed expectations because.. the lunch menu. Good stuff. Healthy. Beautiful decor. David is a great baker.
Enjoyed the donut. Loved the atmosphere.
Not that good. The fruit tart was basically a flattened dinner roll with bitter fruit on it.

I work just up the road and decided to stop in this week for breakfast and dessert. The orange white chocolate mousse almond cake was to die for and the braised short rib sandwich was amazing! The meat just melts in your mouth with flavor. …
Best Croissant anywhere
Everything is great here. Light, buttery, crunchy, fresh. A delight.
Fresh ingredients, delicious food and amazing pastries!
Very flaky croissant’s, delicious braised short rib breakfast sandwich.  Tons of other sandwiches to try.
When you and your husband decide to share and after one bite goes to buy his own....you know that's the good stuff!!!

We were in Nashville this past weekend to celebrate my 50th birthday. My husband had pre-ordered a cake from D'Andrews Bakery and had it delivered to the restaurant where we were celebrating. D'Andrews came through without a glitch!! The …

Can’t recommend this place enough!!! We had a fantastic experience on a Saturday morning around 9. It wasn’t too busy so we received our order really fast. We all got breakfast sandwiches (the veggie one was LOADED with guacamole) and they …
Incredible pastries...we love Jess...and Miss Dixie

Stopped in for a quick lunch while visiting from out of town. The staff was incredibly friendly and helpful, and all the baked goods looked phenomenal. I had a wonderful salad and a delicious dessert. Can't wait to try their sandwiches the next time I'm in town.
It was amazing

A nice place to enjoy a quiet breakfast or lunch. I like the salad options and I frequently get the Veggie sandwich. The also have tons of tasty treats to choose from. If you’re lucky you may see Miss Dixie, she’s sweeter than the treats.
If you haven't been to this place yet, you're missing out! Great coffee at a great price point! Workers are always friendly & helpful!
Food is always great, and fresh. Customer service on the other hand needs improvement.
I definitely love their chocolate chunk cookies and my daughter said their macaroons were the best she's ever eaten. We will definitely be returning.
Fantastic breakfast sandwiches. Great pastries. The service was amazing. I will make this a traditional stop on my Nashville visits.

When visiting Nashville, we originally wanted to go to Puckett's Grocery and Restaurant, but there was a long line out of the door at 11 AM on Sunday.  Instead, we walked a block or two back to D'Andrews for breakfast.  I enjoyed the veggie …
A surprising find on the way to the Ryman...get the doughnut, it's amazing!
Oh the puppy!
Very good food, nice location and fair prices
The food here is really incredible. Nashville gem.

My husband and I plus a couple of friends of ours ate here for breakfast both mornings we were in Nashville visiting from Ohio. We got the bacon, egg, and cheese sandwich both days. It was delicious! We also stopped to get a couple donuts to take home for our in-laws and they raved about the pecan roll. Very polite staff both days.
Loving this place more every visit. Good coffee, great pastry, tasty pizza, and an amazing salad option. The service is always good no matter if they are empty or full.
Best breakfast spot in town

Super well located, everything tasted.good. the chocolate croissant was.awesome. the coffee was.good. the staff super helpful, restrooms clean and the general interior design invites you to get in. Highly recommend.

I had researched places in Nashville to order a cake and Macaroons for my sister in law’s birthday prior to our trip and decided on D’Andrews because of the great reviews. I assure you I was not disappointed. I went there shortly after …

This place is absolutely charming and the food, coffee and service is phenomenal. My husband and I had breakfast sandwiches and were so incredibly surprised at the taste, the freshness of the bread and the explosive taste. Simply yummy. So impressive!!!

Great food options and the coffee was pretty good too.  Had an enjoyable experience here. The staff is friendly and hospitable to your needs. You feel welcomed and you feel like you got your money's worth. Good bang for the buck. Highly recommend to my friends,  A+++++

Delicious little bakery with yummy unique pastries. Everything looked very fresh and just made.  You could see the chefs working behind the glass.  :)  I got a scrumptious BEC (bacon egg cheese) sandwich....so good gooey and savory... a …

This bakery is amazing. The chef, David Andrews, worked at some great establishments (like Gotham Bar and Grill in New York) before returning home to Nashville to launch his bakery. The pastries are beautiful and, more importantly, …
Nashville had a dearth of good sandwich shops downtown. This one is fantastic! I eat here almost everyday now.
Very clean, trendy spot downtown for fresh baked goods, coffee and tea. A little on the pricey side but a good alternative to chains in the area.
Best Coffee I've had in a while...just something extra good about it. Pricey but worth it.
Nice little bakery with good pastries and drinks. Cool interior and friendly staff.

Finally had the time to visit D'Andrews Bakery and Cafe...if you have not yet... GO!  Amazing bakery with tasteful, creative, yummy and not over the top.  We enjoyed creative fun sandwiches and amazing pastries.  I"m from the NY area and …

New York pastry chef has brought delicious pastries and food to downtown Nashville, in a bright and airy modern space. Loved the short ribs breakfast sandwich and the pastries were so good, I took home a box full. My little grandson chowed down on the huge eclair.

I can't say enough amazing things about D'Andrews Bakery! Their delicious treats are out of this world, and their customer service is too! I had an issue with an order that was supposed to be delivered through a delivery app, and the driver …
The pistachio and jam croissants was really good!
Simply one of the bet bakeries in the USA.   Love the donut.
This is my go to coffee shop/bakery! We love this place. Wonderful service and incredible food!
Amazing little bakery right downtown.  They bake everything in house, and have sandwiches and drinks.    Give them a try!

We got a handful of the different sandwiches and pastries and were very impressed with all of them. It's clear they use high quality ingredients - the breads, meats, cheeses, etc.  The staff was very friendly, too.  I would definitely recommend this place.

Wonderful Bakery.   Quality sandwiches on the freshest bread downtown, not "too chefy".   If you are coming to downtown Nashville, make sure you experience this bakery run by a native Nashvillian.   Double Chocolate cookie, Jack Daniels brownie or the Pork Club sandwich are a must try.

Delish! The breakfast sandwiches are served on wonderfully prepared fresh bread and the pastries are the perfect way to start your day. The fritter was our favorite that we tried, next time we will have to save room for the donut! A super friendly staff tops it all off as a cant miss breakfast spot in downtown.
The setting is nice but that’s about it. The hot chocolate was one of the worst I’ve ever drank and a small cup was 6$... I will not be coming back.
Delicious, fresh pastries and the coffee and tea were amazing!!
Breakfast sandwiches and pastries are phenomenal. Highly recommend if in the area!
This is an outstanding find! Easily among some of the best bakeries in the country!  Everything is made fresh on site. It is a terrific place. We will be back!
Best breakfast sandwiches I've ever had.
The best egg sandwich I’ve ever had in my life. Super friendly, great service, good WiFi. Only downside is parking but it’s SO worth it. Go here.

Beyond 5 stars!!! MUST TRY! I always say, if I'm going to eat baked goods, it's got to be worth the calories... AND THIS IS!!! Great experience from start to finish! Delicious everything, great service and clean. Been in Nashville for 3 days, went in everyday... and very friendly staff and owner

We stopped here for a celebratory sweet for our Anniversary—literally the best Carrot Cake and Donuts we have ever eaten! We plan to make a stop back by before we go up north! If you’re in Nashville, stop here! The staff is fantastic and you won’t be let down!

I had the bacon breakfast sandwich (the B.E.C.) and it was by far one of the best breakfast sandwiches I’ve ever had. It’s small for the price but we’ll worth it- highly recommend. I can’t wait to try the actual pastries!
Great little spot right next to the library. Cozy atmosphere, even better treats and coffee.

My first trip to Nashville and we made the wise choice to visit D'Andrews Bakery and cafe. We had breakfast sandwiches and coffee to start, both of the sandwiches were excellent, as was the coffee. Then we just had to get some of the …

Very friendly service, great espresso and delicious pastries. Their pain au chocolat is one of the best I've had, and definitely the nicest looking! I had breakfast twice here while I was in Nashville, I didn't have the chance to try their lunch options but I'm sure they are also great.

Great bakery. Lovely spot for coffee & danish. Their "donut" is wonderful, then there is the pecan cinnamon roll.  Oh my, just pure deliciousness.  We made several visits including for lunch. I highly recommend the roast beef sandwich. Staff & owner are all about customer service. A must visit place while in Nashville.

D’Andrews is one of my favorite places in Nashville and I have been telling any and everyone they must go and eat all the things. The bacon egg + cheese is the most delicious breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had and I would eat one every single …

The staff was super friendly, helping us decide what to choose from the pastry and dessert menu. They passed out free warm chocolate chunk cookies since it was downtown employee appreciation week for Nashville even though we were tourists. …
Amazing pastries.
Fast and friendly service, yummy food. Would recommend if you just need a quick bite for breakfast or lunch.

The pastries are some of the best I have ever had in Nashville. As for the sandwiches.... The chicken sausage sandwich is probably one of the best tasting sandwiches I've ever had. Dont sleep on their lunch menu if you stop by!
Amazing service and treats!
Excellent staff and great lunch selections. Iced coffee is delicious.

Very new cafe where the owner comes in to bake fresh every day at 3am. the pastries are tasty, less tooth achingly sweet compared to others. the yuzu eclair was my jam, tart and fresh with some nice chocolate on top. short walk from the library as well.
So many tasty items on the menu. Great selection of cold teas and kombucha. D'Andrews had a pear brioche on my last visit. I've enjoyed the fritters. I'm looking forward to the expanding lunch menu.
Fantastic food and excellent coffee
Great small place. Brand new and the cold drinks are super refreshing!. Loves the croissants and if you're a fan of freshly backed pastriea, this is a must! :)
Good coffee and a good food assortment and a great team!
New bakery, in downtown. Welcoming and delicious. The chef/ owner is a Nashville native who came "home" after many years in New York.
